8. Rules and Restrictions
Training from Scratch: You must train your model from scratch. You are not allowed to load any pretrained weights (e.g., from ImageNet, CLIP, or models pretrained on other physical datasets). The goal is to learn representations from scratch on the provided dataset.
Model Size Limit: The total number of parameters in your model must be strictly fewer than 100 Million parameters. However, do not blindly increase the parameter count. Because this is high-dimensional spatiotemporal (video) data, the computational cost and memory footprint (VRAM) of intermediate activations are extremely high. For context, the baseline JEPA model only uses ~3.3M parameters in total (~2.5M for the encoder and ~0.8M for the predictor) but can still consume nearly 100 GB of VRAM with a batch size of 8.
Data Scope: You may only use the active_matter dataset provided. No external data is allowed.
No Training on Validation/Test Data: You may only use the training split to update model weights. The validation split is strictly for hyperparameter tuning and model selection. The test split must only be used for final evaluation and cannot be used for any form of training, unsupervised updates, or tuning.
Linear Probing and kNN Only: When evaluating your frozen representations, you must evaluate using both a single linear layer and kNN. Complex regression heads (e.g., MLPs, attention pooling) are not allowed for the final evaluation metric.
