11. FAQ
Can we use CLIP/DINO/VideoMAE pretrained weights?
No. Training from scratch only.
Can we use external unlabeled data?
No.
Can we fine-tune the entire backbone for our main submission?
No. Your core method must be representation learning. You must evaluate using both a single linear layer and kNN on top of a frozen backbone. You may, however, train an end-to-end supervised model strictly to serve as a baseline comparison in your report.
Are we required to train an end-to-end supervised baseline?
It is not mandatory. Comparing your representation learning method against a purely supervised baseline provides insights into the value of your approach.
Are we graded on speed?
Not directly. Report compute fairly; efficiency is appreciated.
How much does the final performance (MSE) affect our grade?
We want you to treat this as a real research project. While strong performance is rewarded, we highly appreciate and reward methodological novelty, rigorous ablation studies, and deep analysis of why a method works or fails.
12. Academic Integrity
Follow the letter and spirit of the rules. Collaborate within your team; do not share code or weights across teams. Cite all external ideas and implementations you reference. Any attempt to train on test set, use pretrained weights, or otherwise circumvent the rules will be considered academic dishonesty and will result in a 0 for the project and a formal report.
